name: HeartKit: AP4 vs AP510
description:
###### Overview

This demo benchmarks multiple advanced AI models running on Ambiq's Apollo4 Blue Plus and Apollo510 EVBs.

values:
##### Normal Sinus Rhythm (NSR) 

A sinus rhythm with a heart rate between 60-100 beats/min.

##### Sinus Bradycardia (SB)

A cardiac rhythm with normal depolarization initiating from the sinus node and a rate of fewer than 60 beats/min.

##### Atrial Fibrillation/Flutter (AFIB/AFL)

**AFIB**: Narrow complex w/ _irregularly irregular_ pattern & no distinguishable p-waves. Ventricular rate b/w 80-180 beats/min.

**AFL**: Narrow complex tachycardia with atria rate of ~300 beats/min. Ventricular rate is a fraction of the rate (e.g. 2: 1).

##### General Supraventricular Tachycardia (GSVT)

GSVT includes heart beats erratically or fast that originate in the atrium or junction of the heart.
